text.value: BENZODIAZEPINE IMMUNOASSAY SCREEN DOES NOT DETECT SOME DRUGS,;INCLUDING LORAZEPAM, CLONAZEPAM, AND FLUNITRAZEPAM.
;METHADONE ASSAY DETECTS METHADONE (NOT OTHER OPIATES/OPIOIDS);QUETIAPINE (SEROQUEL) MAY CAUSE A FALSE POSITIVE RESULT;.
;OPIATE ASSAY DOES NOT RELIABLY DETECT SYNTHETIC OPIOIDS;SUCH AS METHADONE, OXYCODONE, FENTANYL, BUPRENORPHINE, TRAMADOL,;NALOXONE, MEPERIDINE. SEE ONLINE LAB MANUAL FOR DETAILS.
BENZODIAZEPINE IMMUNOASSAY SCREEN DOES NOT RELIABLY DETECT SOME DRUGS,;INCLUDING LORAZEPAM, CLONAZEPAM, AND FLUNITRAZEPAM.
POSITIVE TRICYCLIC RESULTS REPRESENT POTENTIALLY TOXIC LEVELS;THERAPEUTIC TRICYCLIC LEVELS WILL TYPICALLY HAVE NEGATIVE RESULTS.
